[?25l[0m[?25l[0m[0m[38;5;12mI'll share my reasoning process[0m[38;5;244m (using tool: thinking)[0m: Now I can see the exact byte sequence:
- `\x1b]9;Response complete\x07` — this is the OSC (Operating System Command) escape sequence
  - `\x1b]` = ESC ] (OSC start)
  - `9;Response complete` = the payload
  - `\x07` = BEL (OSC terminator)

This is the reliable delimiter to detect when kiro-cli has finished responding.

Also interesting: the response text appears BEFORE the "Response complete" marker. So the pattern is:
1. Agent output text
2. `\x1b]9;Response complete\x07`
3. Credits line

Now let me also check:
- The `mcp.noInteractiveTimeout` setting (30000 - this is likely milliseconds = 30 seconds, which is the MCP init timeout for --no-interactive mode)
- Whether we can override `chat.disableAutoCompaction` per-session

